<blockquote><html>The <b>diamond-square algorithm</b> is a method for generating <a href="/wiki/Heightmap" title="Heightmap">heightmaps</a> for <a href="/wiki/Computer_graphics" title="Computer graphics">computer graphics</a>. It is a slightly better algorithm than the three-dimensional implementation of the midpoint displacement algorithm which produces two-dimensional landscapes. It is also known as the <b>random midpoint displacement fractal</b>, the <b>cloud fractal</b> or the <b>plasma fractal</b>, because of the <a href="/wiki/Plasma_effect" title="Plasma effect">plasma effect</a> produced when applied.</html></blockquote>

